-- CTC Media’s TV Weekly Audience Gains in Russia, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-08-23T19:02:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-23/ctc-media-s-tv-weekly-audience-gains-in-russia-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel saw its average daily share of Russian viewers rise in
the week to Aug. 19, according to TNS-Global.  The share of Russian viewers aged 18 years and older for
CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source
of revenue, climbed to 5.3 percent in the week to Aug. 19 from
4.8 percent a week earlier, TNS-Global said by e-mail today. CTC
advanced to sixth most-watched TV channel in the week to Aug. 19
from seventh a week earlier.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over gained to 5.9 percent in the week to Aug. 19 from 5.2
percent in the previous week, the data show. CTC rose to fifth
most-watched TV channel from sixth last week, outpacing Fifth
Channel, the researcher said.  Russia’s NTV Television, Rossiya-1, Pervyi Kanal and TNT TV
were the top four most watched channels in both categories.
Fifth Channel placed ahead of CTC among viewers 18 years and
older, the data show.  To contact the reporters on this story:
